-Deployment Checklist
1. Dynamic port binding
-listen to the port they tell us
-heroku has different port, we should make sure our app comply to heroku's port
-environment variable is a specific variable that run on a specific node runtime
2. Specify Node Environment
-We want to use specific version of node, so we need to tell heroku which version
of node we want to use
3. Specify start script
-Instruct Heroku what command to run to start our server running
4. Create .gitignore
-We don't want to exlude our node_modules
